  "method": [
    {
      "post_notes": [],
      "pre_notes": [],
      "type": "METHOD_STEP",
      "text": "Soak the beans overnight, and then drain"
    },
    {
      "post_notes": [],
      "pre_notes": [],
      "type": "METHOD_STEP",
      "text": "Roughly chop the greens and herbs, and then combine the fava beans, spring onions, leeks, coriander, parsley, crushed garlic and water in a large bowl"
    },
    {
      "post_notes": [],
      "pre_notes": [],
      "type": "METHOD_STEP",
      "text": "Chop everything very finely in a blender. Transfer the mix to a sieve, and leave until <span class=\"quantity\">200</span>ml of the water has drained out (The water can be drained faster by squeezing in cheesecloth)"
    },
    {
      "post_notes": [],
      "pre_notes": [],
      "type": "METHOD_STEP",
      "text": "Add the remaining seasonings to the batter"
    },
    {
      "post_notes": [],
      "pre_notes": [],
      "type": "METHOD_STEP",
      "text": "Beat thoroghly with an electric whisk until the batter aquires a lighter more mousse-like consistency"
    },
    {
      "post_notes": [],
      "pre_notes": [],
      "type": "METHOD_STEP",
      "text": "Heat the oil to 180C"
    },
    {
      "post_notes": [],
      "pre_notes": [],
      "type": "METHOD_STEP",
      "text": "Prepare the topping by roughly crushing the coriander and sesame seeds with a mortar and pestle, grinder or food processor"
    },
    {
      "post_notes": [],
      "pre_notes": [],
      "type": "METHOD_STEP",
      "text": "Form the falafel either by spooning straight into the oil or using the method <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7RLQfCXdr-g\">here</a>. The video method is actually much easier than it looks. As you form them, dip them in the topping, or sprinkle it on top before adding them to the oil"
    }
  ],
  "notes": [
    {
      "text": "The main reason for the water in this recipe is that it makes the blending much easier. Maybe with a food processor, it wouldn't be necessary"
    },
    {
      "text": "How you form the balls will have a big effect on the texture, so avoid squeezing them into balls as they'll be too dense"
    },
    {
      "text": "This should freeze well, but it deteriorates overnight in the fridge"
    }
  ],
  "title": "Egyptian Falafel (Ta'ameya)",
